From Dan Sorenson Subject Re Boom Dog attack Ryan Cousineau writes Riding up the hill leading to my house I encountered a liver and white Springer Spaniel no relation to the Springer Softail or the Springer Spagthorpe a close relation to the Spagthorpe Viking I must have missed the article on the Spagthorpe Was that the one with the little illuminated Dragon's Head on the front fender a style later copied by Indian and the round side covers accident deleted What worries me about the accident is this I don't think I could have prevented it except by traveling much slower than I This is not necessarily an unreasonable suggestion for a residential area but I was riding around the speed You can forget this line of When an animal decides to take you there's nothing you can do about It has something to do with their I was putting along at a mere or so gravel road with few loose rocks on it as in just like bad concrete and of swinging beef jumped a fence came out of the ditch and rammed me When I saw her jump the fence I went for the gas since she was about feet ahead of me but a good forty to the Damn cow literally chased me down and nailed No damage to cow a bent case guard and a severely annoyed rider were the only If I had my shotgun I'd still be eating Nope if of cow can hit me when I'm actively evading forget a much more manueverable Just run them Dan Sorenson DoD ISU only censors what I read not what I Don't blame USENET Post to exotic distant Meet exciting unusual And flame